{
  "texts": [
    "Retrieval Augmented GenerationRather than fine-tuning, then, we advocate for an approach called Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG).",
    "RAG is an approach whereby documents written by the course teaching team are ingested into a readily searchable database.",
    "When a query is made to the chatbot, the most semantically related portions of the documents are retrieved and provided as part of the input prompt to the chatbot.",
    "This provides the ground truth information, and the LLM can be prompted to review the retrieved background data and to base its responses on that.In our experience, RAG comes with several major benefits over fine-tuning.",
    "First, since it is based on retrieving information from documents written by the teaching team, someone who is not an expert in the use of LLMs but is an expert in the course concepts can write the documents and provide them to the LLM via an easy-touse interface."
  ]
}